description: India is set to become the largest hub for Trump Towers outside the US, with plans to expand from four to ten properties in the next six years.  Tribeca Developers, Trump's Indian partner, announced the expansion following Trump's presidential victory, citing his confidence in India's potential under Prime Minister Modi's leadership.
title: India said to have most Trump Towers outside US

description: Medical colleges in India are facing scrutiny for a disproportionately high number of ragging complaints, with over 40% of all complaints originating from these institutions.  Anti-ragging activists argue that despite the alarming number of complaints, including cases resulting in student suicides,  colleges and authorities often fail to take appropriate action, highlighting the urgent need for effective anti-ragging measures and accountability.
title: Activists claim UGC cell sitting on ragging plaints

description: Driven by a favorable monsoon season, rural India witnessed a surge in FMCG consumption during the September quarter, outpacing urban growth.  While rural areas thrived, urban consumption remained subdued due to high food inflation impacting middle-class spending.
title: At 6%, rural FMCG growth 2x of urban

description: India's Solar Energy Corporation of India (SECI) has banned Reliance Power and its subsidiaries from bidding on its contracts for three years. SECI alleges that Reliance Power submitted a fake bank guarantee as part of a bid for a battery energy storage system project. Reliance Power maintains it was the victim of fraud and plans to challenge the ban.
title: PSU Solar bars R-Power, arms from contracts

description: The Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India (IBBI) has put forward proposals to streamline the insolvency process for real estate projects.  These proposals aim to allow the registration of properties owned by insolvent real estate companies if homebuyers have cleared dues and received possession.  The IBBI also suggests that homebuyers should be exempt from certain eligibility criteria when bidding for such projects.
title: Allow registration in insolvency cases if OC issued: IBBI

description: Indian philanthropists donated a total of Rs 8,783 crore in FY24, a modest increase from the previous year. Shiv Nadar topped the list for the fourth consecutive year, donating Rs 2,153 crore, primarily towards education. The EdelGive-Hurun India Philanthropy List 2024 highlights the growing trend of substantial donations among India's wealthiest individuals.
title: Charity by India Inc up 4%, Nadar biggest giver

description: A station master's casual "OK" during a heated phone argument with his wife was misconstrued as authorization to dispatch a train. This mistake cost the railways Rs 3 crore and led to the station master's suspension, fueling a tumultuous 12-year divorce battle that ultimately reached the Chhattisgarh High Court.
title: Station master's 'OK' sends train, his life on wrong track

description: The Indian rupee fell to a new low against the US dollar, closing at 84.37, driven by foreign investors selling equities and a strengthening dollar following Donald Trump's presidential victory. Despite outperforming some Asian currencies, the rupee faced pressure from strong dollar demand. Analysts predict further depreciation before potential recovery, contingent on global factors like the situation in West Asia and the impact of Trump's policies.
title: Re hits record low of 84.38 as dollar surges after Trump win

description: The Supreme Court has ordered the liquidation of Jet Airways after the Jalan Kalrock Consortium, the winning bidder, failed to deposit the first installment of the resolution plan. The court invoked its special powers to order the liquidation, citing the consortium's violations and the lack of progress in reviving the airline.
title: End of runway for Jet: SC orders liquidation, nixes revival plan

description: Delhi police arrested three men in connection with the gang rape of a 34-year-old woman researcher on October 11th. The accused, identified through CCTV footage and witness testimonies, allegedly assaulted the woman near ITO and abandoned her in Sarai Kale Khan.  Police are ensuring the accused face the harshest punishment under the law.
title: Auto driver among three held for raping researcher near ITO in Oct

description: NCP leader Ajit Pawar criticized Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath's divisive rhetoric during his Maharashtra campaign. Pawar emphasized Maharashtra's tradition of communal harmony and pledged support for his party's candidate, Nawab Malik, who faces money laundering allegations. He also questioned the financial viability of the MVA's campaign promises.
title: After Yogi’s ‘batenge…’ slogan in Maha, ally Ajit slams divisive ‘outsiders’

description: The Supreme Court proposed that the Delhi Development Authority, responsible for illegally cutting down 1,670 trees, plant double that number in the southern ridge and a hundred times that across Delhi as compensation. The court also sought a mechanism to prevent future illegal tree felling in the city's vital green areas.
title: SC proposes planting 2x trees felled in Ridge, order to be passed today

description: To combat rising air pollution, India has doubled the fines for farmers burning crop residue in several northern states.  The increased penalties, ranging from Rs 5,000 to Rs 30,000, took effect immediately. Despite a decrease in burning this season, over 400,000 cases have been reported across six states, with Punjab accounting for the majority.
title: Centre doubles penalty for stubble burning

description: The Indian Air Force, Navy, and Coast Guard are terminating their agreements with Uber due to concerns about data security and potential location tracking of military personnel. Despite initial measures to protect data, the decision to scrap the contracts follows public controversy and aims to mitigate potential risks.
title: IAF, Navy start process to scrap cab aggregator deal over security fears

description: India accused Canada of hypocrisy regarding freedom of speech after Canada blocked an Australian publication, Australia Today, for highlighting Indian Foreign Minister S Jaishankar's criticisms of Canada.  India also stated Canada failed to provide security for Indian consular camps despite increased threats against Indian diplomats, leading to the cancellation of some camps.
title: India slams 'hypocrisy' of Canada on free speech

description: The Supreme Court ruled that eligibility criteria for government jobs cannot be changed after advertising vacancies. The court emphasized that transparency and non-discrimination are crucial in public recruitment, and any changes must be justified and adhere to Article 14 of the Constitution.
title: SC: Eligibility criteria can’t be changed after advertising vacancy

description: Rahul Gandhi faced criticism from descendants of Indian royal families, including BJP minister Jyotiraditya Scindia, for claiming in an opinion piece that the East India Company exploited Indian rulers.  Scindia accused Gandhi of historical ignorance and harboring a colonial mindset.  Congress defended Gandhi, suggesting his critics were merely demonstrating loyalty to their current political affiliations.
title: Scindia, other ex-royals slam Rahul for remark on British ties with 'pliant maharajas'

description: India's Home Minister Amit Shah announced that the country is developing a national counter-terrorism policy and strategy.  The plan, to be unveiled in 2025, aims to create a unified approach to combating terrorism across all agencies.  Shah emphasized the need for state police forces to take a leading role, supported by central agencies, in implementing the strategy.
title: National anti-terror plan for central, state agencies coming in 2025: Shah
23 years on, supplier of killer hooch that claimed 53 lives arrested in TN

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) is investigating Amazon and Flipkart for potential violations of foreign exchange regulations. The probe, stemming from complaints about unfair business practices, focuses on allegations that the e-commerce giants manipulate pricing and disadvantage smaller vendors. While searches were conducted at vendor locations, the ED hasn't targeted Amazon or Flipkart directly yet.
title: Fema case: ED searches sites tied to e-tailers

description: White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre attributed the Democrats' election losses partly to global challenges affecting incumbent leaders worldwide. “There’s going to be a lot of punditry, a lot of election experts who are going to have their opinions, who are going to have their thoughts, but the president is very, very proud of what he’s been able to accomplish and incredibly impressed with what the vice president was able to do,” Jean-Pierre said.
title: 'Global headwinds' blamed for election result in first White House briefing since Nov 5

description: The Supreme Court overturned its own 2021 ruling, granting the Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs the authority to pursue notices amounting to Rs 20,000 crore in potentially unpaid customs duties. The court recognized the designation of DRI officers as 'proper officers' for issuing these notices, validating a 2011 notification and a retrospective amendment in the 2022 Finance Act.
title: SC lets customs revive notices for Rs20k cr duty

description: 111-year-old Fulamati Sarkar, a resident of Gadchiroli, Maharashtra, is set to become one of the oldest voters in the upcoming assembly elections.  Despite her age and the availability of home voting, Fulamati is determined to personally cast her vote, inspiring many with her dedication to democracy. The district administration has named her the SVEEP icon for her unwavering commitment.
title: In Maoist stronghold, 111-year-old refuses home-vote, to go to booth

description: Devendra Fadnavis, at a Yavatmal rally, accused Rahul Gandhi of insulting the Constitution by distributing blank red books disguised as the Constitution at a Nagpur event.  Gandhi's supporters clarified that the books were red-covered notepads designed around a pocket-sized Constitution, while Fadnavis criticized Gandhi's stance on reservations and highlighted BJP's efforts for the marginalized communities.
title: Fadnavis: Cong’s ‘red book’ with blank pages insulted Constitution

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized Devendra Fadnavis for his remarks about the display of the Constitution at a Nagpur event, calling it an insult to Ambedkar. Gandhi accused the BJP of attacking the Constitution and vowed that the people of Maharashtra would retaliate in the Lok Sabha elections. Congress spokesperson Jairam Ramesh also condemned Fadnavis's statement, highlighting the RSS's historical criticism of the Constitution.
title: Rahul: People will avenge 'attack' on Constitution

description: The Shiv Sena (UBT) released its election manifesto, pledging to reclaim land given to the Adani Group for the Dharavi redevelopment, construct an IFSC in Dharavi, and develop recreation facilities on the eastern seafront. The party also promised to implement the OPS for government employees, pursue free local train travel for women, and establish a Gig Workers Welfare Board.
title: If MVA wins, will take back Dharavi land given to Adani: UBT manifesto

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin congratulated Donald Trump on his US election victory, expressing hope for improved relations. While welcoming Trump's stated desire to restore ties and address the Ukrainian crisis, the Kremlin remains cautious, awaiting concrete policy proposals. Putin acknowledged the uncertainty surrounding Trump's second term and emphasized the US's role in strained relations.
title: Russia's Putin congratulates Donald Trump on his victory

description: The Uttar Pradesh State Women's Commission has proposed new safety guidelines to protect women in public spaces. These guidelines include requiring female staff in women's clothing stores and on school buses, as well as mandating female trainers in gyms and yoga studios. The commission is also considering prohibiting male tailors from taking women's measurements.
title: No male tailor should take women’s measurements, proposes UP panel

description: The BJP has condemned a resolution passed by the INDIA alliance in the Jammu and Kashmir assembly to restore the region's special status. BJP leader Smriti Irani called the resolution an attempt to "wage war against the Indian constitution" and accused the alliance of supporting terrorists and separatists. Irani asserted that the BJP would not allow the abrogation of Article 370 to be reversed.
title: Resolution to restore Article 370 an attempt to divide India: BJP

description: Following a controversial social media post in Chittagong, Bangladesh, clashes erupted between the Hindu community and law enforcement, resulting in property damage. India has called upon the interim government in Dhaka to take decisive action against extremist elements and ensure the safety of Hindus in the country.
title: Protect Hindus, India tells Dhaka amid fresh clashes

description: Central intelligence agencies have issued high alerts to northeastern states, particularly Assam and Tripura, regarding clandestine activities of Jamaat-ul-Mujahideen Bangladesh (JMB).  Increased surveillance and recent arrests of suspected operatives highlight concerns about the group's territorial expansion efforts.  Authorities emphasize the need for coordinated efforts to combat infiltration and maintain border security.
title: Terror alert in NE over Bangladesh outfits’ plan to target region

description: The National Tiger Conservation Authority (NTCA) is investigating the disappearance of 25 tigers from Ranthambore Tiger Reserve in Rajasthan. While the state forest department claims to have found evidence of 10 tigers, concerns remain about poaching and retaliatory killings. Overcrowding in the reserve is also a concern, as tigers are moving closer to human settlements.
title: NTCA orders probe into 25 missing tigers of Ranthambore

description: The Kerala High Court ruled that media freedom is not absolute and must be exercised within constitutional boundaries. The court emphasized that while reporting on criminal cases, the media must respect the separation of powers and refrain from declaring guilt or innocence before a judicial verdict.
title: Can't restrict media's right to expression except by law: HC

description: The Delhi High Court dismissed a petition challenging the import ban on Salman Rushdie's "The Satanic Verses."  The court deemed the petition 'infructuous' as authorities couldn't locate the 1988 notification imposing the ban.  The bench concluded that without the notification, its validity couldn't be assessed.
title: 'Satanic Verses' ban order missing, have to presume it doesn't exist: HC

description: The Supreme Court has mandated that all trial courts must provide compensation to survivors of sexual assault and acid attack cases, regardless of the accused's conviction or acquittal. This directive aims to ensure that victims receive financial support and that the victim compensation scheme outlined in Indian law is effectively implemented.
title: Assault survivors must receive aid irrespective of outcome of case: SC

description: Three individuals, Abbas Ali, Shamsun Kareem Raj, and Dawood Suleiman, affiliated with the banned terrorist group Base Movement, were sentenced to life imprisonment for the 2016 Kollam collectorate blast. The court found them guilty of using an improvised explosive device, causing terror and injuring one person. A fourth suspect was acquitted due to insufficient evidence.
title: 3 get life term in Kollam collectorate blast case

description: Bakhtawar Ali, a home guard accused of orchestrating a violent clash during Muharram in Bareilly, has been detained under the National Security Act. The clash resulted in one fatality and numerous injuries, prompting the demolition of 14 houses and multiple arrests. Ali's family claims he is being scapegoated, alleging the violence was instigated by both sides.
title: Muharram clash: NSA on ‘mastermind’ home guard

description: Two village defense guards were tragically killed in Kishtwar, Jammu, by the Kashmir Tigers, a group linked to Jaish-e-Mohammed. The group claimed responsibility and threatened others who support security forces. This incident follows a series of terrorist attacks and heightened security operations in Jammu and Kashmir, highlighting the volatile situation in the region.
title: Jaish terrorists killed two village guards in Jammu’s Kishtwar

description: Real estate developer and film producer Anita Verma-Lallian recently purchased Matthew Perry's former Los Angeles home for $8.55 million. Lallian, who performed a puja ceremony at the residence, emphasized that her decision to buy the property was driven by her admiration for the home itself, not its previous ownership.
title: Indian-origin woman explains why she bought Matthew Perry's house

description: Ireland's Data Protection Commission fined LinkedIn €310 million for violating data privacy regulations. The investigation focused on LinkedIn's use of personal data for targeted advertising. The commission found LinkedIn's practices non-compliant with GDPR standards on user consent and data usage. LinkedIn must now adjust its data processing practices. The ruling highlights the EU's commitment to protecting data privacy.
title: LinkedIn fined €310 million by Ireland’s data watchdog for privacy violations

description: A tragic accident in Jammu & Kashmir's Reasi district claimed the lives of four individuals, including a young girl. The driver of an SUV lost control, causing the vehicle to plummet into a gorge. Three occupants died at the scene, while another succumbed to injuries at the hospital. Two others are currently receiving medical treatment.
title: Father, daughter among 4 killed in accident in J&K

description: Indian banks are phasing out ATMs and cash recyclers despite record cash circulation. The shift is attributed to the rising popularity of digital payments and a focus on digital transformation. While cash remains significant in the Indian economy, ATM penetration is low.
title: UPI, RBI rules ...: Why Banks are shutting down ATMs

description: Chaos erupted in the Jammu and Kashmir assembly as BJP and National Conference MLAs clashed over a resolution demanding the restoration of Article 370.  The speaker evicted BJP members for disrupting the proceedings, leading to physical altercations with marshals. BJP termed the resolution a futile attempt, while other parties criticized their stance and the disruption.
title: Brawls erupt in J&K assembly over resolution to restore 370

description: An Indian-American woman, Saba Haider, originally from Ghaziabad, has won a seat on the DuPage County Board in Illinois, US. Despite a grueling campaign that left her physically exhausted, Saba persevered, attributing her success to her supportive family and dedicated community engagement.
title: In Trump moment, a Democrat win lights up an NCR house

description: "I've thought this for a while, but yesterday confirmed it for me. I don't see my future being in the United States. Even if he's only in office for 4 years, even if the anti-trans regulations magically don't happen, the people who willingly voted this in are not going anywhere anytime soon," Elon Musk's estranged daughter Vivian Jenna Wilson posted on Threads.
title: Elon Musk's estranged daughter says she has no future in Trump's US: 'Even if...'

description: Zomato co-founder Deepinder Goyal and Infosys founder Narayana Murthy, along with their wives, recently appeared on The Great Indian Kapil Show.  Goyal humorously addressed Zomato's playful notifications, revealing that he sometimes forwards messages intended for his wife to the marketing team.  Murthy and his wife entertained the audience with their charming interactions and anecdotes.
title: Deepinder Goyal reveals the secret of flirty texts for his app's notifications

description: Odisha minister Krushna Chandra criticised former CM Naveen Patnaik's claims that the BJP government's actions led to deaths from consuming mango kernel gruel. Chandra argued that Patnaik's party had done nothing for the state during their tenure, citing Patnaik's inability to speak Odia fluently as evidence.
title: BJP on Patnaik's 'penance' attack: 'Would've spoken Odia properly'
J&K: Terrorists kill two in Kishtwar; encounter underway in Sopore

description: TV actor Nitin Chauhaan, known for his roles in shows like "Tera Yaar Hoon Main" and "Splitsvilla 5," tragically passed away at the age of 36. The actor died by suicide, leaving his family and friends in shock. Chauhaan's close friend shared that the actor had not expressed any struggles, making his sudden passing even more heartbreaking.
title: Tera Yaar Hoon Main and Splitsvilla 5 fame Nitin Chauhaan passes away at 36

description: Suryakumar Yadav on Thursday revealed how Rohit Sharma's emphasis on balance, both on and off the field, has shaped his own leadership style as India's T20I captain.  India's premier T20 batter Surya emphasises the importance of spending time with teammates, understanding their mindsets, and fostering a supportive environment to enhance on-field performance.
title: 'Balance is important, even if you...': Surya reveals Rohit's philosophy

description: The World Meteorological Organization reports that 2024 is on track to be the hottest year on record, potentially exceeding the 1.5 degrees Celsius warming threshold set by the Paris Agreement. This projection, based on data from January to September, surpasses the previous record set in 2023.
title: Year 2024 is on track to be warmest year on record: WMO

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) might adjust the 2025 Champions Trophy schedule. According to sources, India's matches could be held in the UAE due to political and security concerns. The PCB aims to announce the schedule by next week. The tournament is scheduled from February 19 to March 9, 2025.
title: Champions Trophy: India likely to play in UAE after PCB...

description: Chaos erupted at Delhi's Geeta Colony Chhath Puja celebrations as devotees arrived to find the artificial ghat devoid of water. Outraged by the lack of preparation, they staged protests, demanding accountability from the Delhi government. BJP councilor Sandeep Kapoor criticized the government's inaction, highlighting the delayed and insufficient water supply.
title: Watch: Chhath puja celebrations without water, Delhi's colony residents protest

description: Donald Trump's return to the White House could bring significant changes to U.S. education policy, including potential reversals of Biden-era reforms on student loans and college oversight.  His administration may also reshape K-12 education, particularly around social issues, and impact international student policies, leaving universities, schools, and students facing a period of both potential opportunity and upheaval.
title: Trump's return could trigger these radical changes in US education policy

description: On a flight from Bengaluru, MS Dhoni, his wife Sakshi, and their daughter Ziva delighted a young fan on her fourth birthday. A video of the heartwarming encounter went viral, showcasing the family's down-to-earth nature. Sakshi's playful interaction with the initially hesitant girl, encouraging her to approach Dhoni, won hearts online.
title: Viral Video: Dhoni's wife Sakshi wins hearts with humble gesture

description: Late night comedians in the US, largely critical of former President Donald Trump, reacted with dismay and shock to his victory in the 2024 Presidential elections. Hosts like Jimmy Kimmel, Stephen Colbert, and Jimmy Fallon expressed disappointment, while some took aim at Trump voters and the political climate that led to his win.
title: Comedians cry as Trump has the last laugh

description: Donald Trump's unexpected victory against Kamala Harris has sent ripples across the globe.  World leaders are cautiously optimistic, yet apprehensive about the potential instability his second term might bring.  Key concerns include heightened trade tensions with China, uncertainty surrounding the Middle East, and potential shifts in US foreign policy towards Russia and Nato.
title: What Trump's return could mean for allies & adversaries

description: Indian tax authorities raided Truecaller offices across India. The searches aimed to investigate potential tax evasion. Truecaller confirmed the searches and pledged full cooperation. The company asserted its compliance with tax regulations. Truecaller emphasized its commitment to transparency and ethical financial practices. The raids come a day after Truecaller appointed Rishit Jhunjhunwala as its new CEO.
title: Truecaller India offices raid: What the company has to say

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat stated that India will overcome all challenges and remain a unifying nation. He emphasized the importance of standing against injustice and upholding righteousness. Bhagwat highlighted the RSS's commitment to supporting the work of 'Sanatan' and saints, even suggesting the use of force against any obstacles.
title: RSS volunteers will clear path for Sanatan, saints with sticks: Mohan Bhagwat

description: Virat Kohli has partnered with Sporting Beyond to manage his business interests. Kohli's recent performance in the New Zealand Test series raised concerns. He will be looking to regain his form in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy. The series against Australia is crucial for India's chances in the ICC World Test Championship.
title: 'I'm excited to announce...': Kohli's post goes viral
Why despite raising $1bn in funds, Harris campaign ended $20m in debt
Indian-Americans who may get top spots in Trump 2.0 Cabinet

description: Despite an energetic campaign, Kamala Harris lost the presidential election to Donald Trump, who benefited from a surge in support from his base and unexpected demographics. Harris's supporters are alleging voter fraud due to a 13 million vote deficit compared to Biden's 2020 performance, while Trump supporters claim it exposes fraud in the previous election.
title: Dems, MAGA trade charges on poll fraud as 2024 turnout is 16m lower than in 2020

description: Bollywood star Shah Rukh Khan received a death threat, prompting increased security measures.  Meanwhile,  Richa Chadha and Ali Fazal delighted fans by announcing their daughter's name, Zuneyra Ida Fazal.  The industry mourns the loss of renowned folk singer Sharda Sinha, whose last rites will be conducted with full state honors.
title: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: French national team coach Didier Deschamps on Thursday announced that star striker Kylian Mbappe will not be playing in the upcoming Nations League matches against Israel and Italy. This is the second consecutive time Mbappe has been left out of the squad, despite having played for Real Madrid in the Champions League earlier this week.
title: Mbappe left out France squad again for Nations League games

description: Elon Musk's net worth soared by $26.5 billion after Donald Trump's victory in the US elections. Musk, a staunch Trump supporter, witnessed a 15% surge in Tesla's shares.
title: How Elon Musk’s $130 million became $26 billion in one flat day

description: A mysterious trader known as the "Trump whale" made nearly $50 million by accurately predicting Donald Trump's 2024 presidential victory on the crypto prediction platform Polymarket.  The trader, identified as Theo, a former French banker, used his financial expertise and skepticism of traditional polling to make data-driven bets that challenged conventional election forecasting.
title: Fredi9999: How a 'Trump whale' won $50m bet on US polls

description: Swetha Kothandan, an Indian student in the UK, has sparked a discussion on the job crisis faced by international students, offering to work for free to secure employment as her visa deadline looms. With rising unemployment and reduced hiring amid the UK's economic slump, many graduates struggle to find opportunities. This situation raises urgent questions about the support systems for international students and the ethical implications of unpaid work in a tightening job market.
title: Is Britain's economic slump the culprit behind the job crisis of Indian students?

description: The Women's Premier League (WPL) is gearing up for the 2025 season with teams strategically retaining their star players. Franchises like Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) and Mumbai Indians (MI) held onto their heavy-hitting lineups, while others balanced their rosters with a mix of domestic and international talent ahead of the mini-auction.
title: WPL 2025: Full list of retained players & remaining purses of all 5 teams

description: Donald Trump won the 2024 presidential election, going against forecasts that projected a close contest. Trump’s victory was largely attributed to his focus on economic discontent, immigration concerns, and cultural divides.
title: 5 simple reasons why Donald Trump easily beat Kamala Harris

description: Arjun Kapoor’s openness about his journey with Hashimoto’s Thyroiditis shines a light on this often misunderstood autoimmune disorder. By sharing his experience, he highlights the importance of early diagnosis and proper management, emphasizing that with the right support, people can lead fulfilling lives despite the condition.  Here's everything we need to know about Hashimoto's Thyroiditis.
title: Arjun Kapoor opens up about his weight fluctuation due to autoimmune disorder

description: The Supreme Court has decided to keep the trial of a Kolkata doctor's rape and murder case within West Bengal. The court stated that the trial court judge has the authority to request further investigations. The trial is set to begin on November 11th, with daily proceedings scheduled.
title: RG Kar rape-murder case: SC declines to shift trial outside West Bengal

description: Donald Trump, with an estimated net worth of $6.49 billion, has secured a second term as the 47th US President after defeating Kamala Harris. His wealth, primarily rooted in real estate and boosted by his company Trump Media & Technology Group, has seen significant growth. Despite facing financial liabilities from lawsuits, Trump's assets, including properties, gold, and cryptocurrency, contribute to his position as one of the wealthiest presidents in US history.
title: Donald Trump net worth: How rich is the next US president?

description: Former India captain Kapil Dev has expressed confidence in Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli's ability to overcome their recent batting slump and deliver strong performances in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy against Australia. Despite a challenging series against New Zealand, Kapil urged the veteran duo to focus, enjoy the game, and draw upon their vast experience to regain their form.
title: 'Forget about NZ series': Kapil Dev to Virat and Rohit

description: Following clashes between Hindus and law enforcement in Chittagong, India has called on Bangladesh to protect its Hindu minority. The unrest erupted after a social media post criticizing ISKCON sparked outrage and violence, with accusations of attacks on Hindu businesses. The incident has heightened tensions and raised concerns about the safety of Hindus in Bangladesh.
title: 'Take strong measures to ensure safety of Hindus': India urges B'desh

description: Astronaut Sunita Williams, initially on an eight-day mission aboard the ISS, faces health concerns as her stay extends to six months due to spacecraft issues.  Recent photos reveal weight loss, prompting worries about nutritional deficiency and the long-term effects of prolonged space travel. NASA prioritizes their health, with a planned return via SpaceX in February.
title: Nasa astronaut Sunita Williams health deteriorates amid extended ISS mission

description: Karnataka minister Priyank Kharge criticised the Joint Parliamentary Committee on the Waqf Amendment Bill, calling it a "BJP-sponsored committee." He questioned the presence of individuals with no connection to the JPC at the meeting.  TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee announced opposition members' boycott of upcoming meetings, citing the chairman's "authoritarian approach" and demanding a less hectic schedule.
title: 'BJP-sponsored committee': Priyank Kharge slams composition of Waqf joint panel

description: Comedian Akaash Singh criticizes the Democratic Party's leadership, particularly Joe Biden's decision to run for re-election and the late Ruth Bader Ginsburg's choice to remain on the Supreme Court. Singh believes these decisions contributed to Donald Trump's election victory.
title: Comedian who hosted Trump rips into democrats: 'They don't ever do anything correctly'

description: The Congress party in Maharashtra has taken disciplinary action against its members contesting against the Maha Vikas Aghadi (MVA) alliance candidates. The party suspended these rebel candidates for a period of six years, emphasizing that there would be no tolerance for "friendly fights" within the alliance.
title: 'No friendly fights in MVA': Cong suspends all rebel candidates for 6 years

description: Meanwhile, Shah Rukh's house Mannat continues to a tourist spot even on the day the actor has received a threat. His fans were spotted outside taking selfies, though cops have barricaded the area, and not allowed them to get close. However, fans are sitting outside with bags and baggages, hoping to catch a glimpse of their superstar
title: Shah Rukh Khan receives death threat: Police barricades surround Mannat,

description: Former Indian cricketer Robin Uthappa criticized Chennai Super Kings (CSK) for allowing New Zealand player Rachin Ravindra to train at their academy before a series against India. Uthappa argued that while CSK are known for supporting its players, national interests should take precedence, especially when it involves a foreign player using the facilities to prepare for a series against India.
title: Uthappa slams CSK for Ravindra's practice facilities, says...

description: Canada's right-wing leaders, inspired by recent Republican victories in the US, are challenging Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's policies. Maxime Bernier, leader of the People's Party of Canada, criticizes Trudeau's stance on immigration, climate change, and government spending, urging for a more conservative approach.
title: Trudeau slammed in Canada for silence over temple attack

description: Music mogul Sean "Diddy" Combs faces serious legal challenges as witness Courtney Burgess alleges possession of explicit tapes, some purportedly involving minors, that expose Combs' alleged misconduct. Burgess claims the tapes were given to him by Combs' former partner, Kim Porter, before her death.
title: Courtney Burgess and Diddy Tapes: How is he connected to Sean Combs?

description: The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) has released a revised examination calendar for 2025, outlining the schedule for various recruitment exams. The calendar includes dates for notifications, application deadlines, and exam commencement. However, UPSC notes that these dates are subject to change based on unforeseen circumstances.
title: UPSC Calendar 2025 revised: Check complete updated schedule here
'Uphold rule of law': MEA to Canada after Brampton temple attack

description: What makes Kash Patel’s views more compelling is his perspective on issues that markedly diverge from those of the US establishment and media. During the Ram Temple consecration, the US Commission on International Religious Freedom (USCIRF) expressed concerns, telling VOA they were “troubled” by the construction of the Ram Temple in Ayodhya. The New York Times described it as “A Triumph Toward a Hindu-First India,” and CNN reported, “Ayodhya Ram Mandir: India PM Modi inaugurates Hindu temple on razed Babri mosque site.” Patel accused Washington newspapers of only covering the past 50 years of history.
title: 'There for 500 yrs': Trump's prospective CIA chief on Ram Mandir

description: India's External Affairs Ministry criticized Canada for blocking the social media channels of "Australia Today" following its broadcast of a press conference featuring Indian Foreign Minister S Jaishankar. During the conference, Jaishankar reiterated India's stance on Canada's allegations, deeming them baseless and highlighting the surveillance faced by Indian diplomats in Canada.
title: 'Hypocrisy': MEA on Canada 'banning' Oz outlet over Jaishankar clip

description: Union Minister Kiren Rijiju has criticised Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge for his remarks about Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Kharge had called Modi "chief of liars" at a Jharkhand rally, accusing him of not fulfilling promises. Rijiju defended Modi, highlighting his global standing and referencing a congratulatory call from former US President Donald Trump.
title: 'Very hurt': BJP's Kiren Rijiju on Kharge's 'choice of words' for PM Modi

description: Sharan Hegde, CEO of 1% Club, announced a 15% workforce reduction as part of a cost-cutting initiative. The financial education platform, which boasts $8 million in annual revenue, is shifting its focus towards AI-driven cost savings.
title: Instagram influencer Sharan Hegde: I just laid off 15% of my workforce & I ...

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) conducted searches on vendors associated with e-commerce giants Amazon and Flipkart as part of an investigation into potential violations of foreign exchange laws. The raids, spanning multiple cities, focused on financial transactions of "preferred" vendors, aiming to uncover any irregularities related to foreign exchange regulations.
title: ED conducts pan-India raids on sellers using Amazon, Flipkart

description: Donald Trump secured a second term as U.S. president with significant support from Elon Musk, who emerged as a powerful force in the Republican's campaign.  Musk's endorsement highlighted the growing influence of tech leaders in politics. Several tech CEOs, including those from Google, Microsoft, Meta, and Apple, publicly congratulated Trump on his victory.

description: While on SRK, he recently celebrated his birthday with his fans at a special event in the city. During the chat, the actor opened up about various aspects of his life, movies, and even his kids Aryan, Suhana and AbRam. In a newly surfaced clip from the fun interaction, Khan also gave a warm shoutout to director Rahul Dholakia and his upcoming film 'Agni'.
title: Death threat issued to Shah Rukh Khan; investigation underway

description: NCP chief Ajit Pawar declared that he will campaign for Nawab Malik in the upcoming Maharashtra assembly elections, despite allegations linking Malik to Dawood Ibrahim. Pawar defended Malik, stating that no charges have been proven.  The ruling Mahayuti alliance, however, refused to support Malik, leading to a four-way contest in the Mankhurd Shivajinagar constituency.
title: 'Nothing proven': Ajit Pawar backs Nawab Malik despite BJP, Sena backlash

description: Smriti Irani, a BJP leader, criticized the INDIA alliance's demand to reinstate Article 370 in Jammu and Kashmir.  She called it an insult to the Indian Constitution and Supreme Court. This follows disruptions in the J&K Assembly over the issue, with BJP and opposition members clashing.  Irani highlighted post-2019 progress in the region, citing reduced violence and increased tourism.
title: 'Aligning with terror': BJP slams INDIA bloc over Art 370 demand

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai congratulated Donald Trump on his election victory, expressing optimism for collaboration to foster innovation.  Other tech leaders, including Microsoft's Satya Nadella, Facebook's Mark Zuckerberg, Apple's Tim Cook, and OpenAI's Sam Altman, also extended their congratulations and looked forward to working with the new administration.
title: Sundar Pichai congratulates Trump on ‘his decisive victory’: ‘We are in a….’

description: Ricky Ponting has advice for Babar Azam on how to regain his batting prowess. Ponting suggests Babar take inspiration from Virat Kohli's successful break from cricket, which allowed Kohli to return refreshed and in top form.
title: Ricky Ponting wants Babar Azam to take Virat Kohli's way to regain form

description: Indian royalty have sharply criticized Rahul Gandhi for his recent comments on the role of princely states during British rule. They accuse him of distorting history and disrespecting the sacrifices made by their ancestors in India's struggle for independence and cultural preservation.
title: Royal scions, BJP leaders slam Rahul’s 'pliant Maharajas' remark

description: Former UK Prime Minister Rishi Sunak and his wife Akshata Murty, daughter of Infosys co-founder N R Narayana Murthy, visited the Raghavendra Swamy Mutt in Bengaluru. The couple, accompanied by Narayana Murthy and his wife Sudha Murty, a Rajya Sabha member, sought blessings and participated in traditional rituals at the temple on Tuesday.
title: Ex-UK PM Sunak visits Raghavendra Swamy Mutt in B'luru with in-laws

description: The BJP criticized Congress for distributing blank copies of the Constitution at Rahul Gandhi's event in Nagpur. They accused Congress of insulting the Constitution and Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, highlighting past instances where Congress leaders opposed reservations and allegedly removed historical figures from the Constitution.
title: 'Insult to Ambedkar': BJP accuses Cong of distributing blank copies of Constitution

description: Truecaller's co-founders, Alan Mamedi and Nami Zarringhalam, are stepping down from their operational roles to become board members and advisors. Rishit Jhunjhunwala, current head of product and managing director of India, will take over as CEO on January 9, 2025. Mamedi and Zarringhalam expressed confidence in Jhunjhunwala's leadership and vision for the company's future.
title: Truecaller names its India MD as global CEO; read co-founders' letter

description: Dhruv Jurel's impressive 80-run knock against Australia 'A' has put him in contention for a place in the playing eleven for the opening Test of the Border Gavaskar Trophy. Jurel's fighting knock might see him replace Sarfaraz Khan in the middle order, but there is a rank outside chance of him opening with Yashasvi Jaiswal.
title: Will Dhruv Jurel's India 'A' show fetch him a place in Perth Test?

description: The US cryptocurrency industry, after investing heavily in recent elections, anticipates a significant regulatory shift with the expected departure of SEC Chair Gary Gensler. President-elect Trump's victory could usher in a more crypto-friendly SEC, potentially replacing Gensler with someone who favors integrating digital assets into existing financial frameworks.
title: Why Donald Trump may fire this US govt official on the first day as US President

description: Bollywood actor Shah Rukh Khan received a death threat over a phone call, leading Mumbai police to file an FIR against an unidentified individual. This incident follows a series of death threats and extortion attempts made by the Lawrence Bishnoi gang against actor Salman Khan, prompting police investigations in both cases.
title: After Salman Khan, Shah Rukh Khan receives death threat

description: The Supreme Court ruled that public sector job criteria cannot be changed mid-recruitment unless rules permit, emphasizing transparency. The court stated that recruitment starts with advertising and ends with filling positions, and any changes must be fair and reasonable.
title: 'Eligibility can't be changed midway': SC on recruitment for govt jobs

description: South Korean researchers have created a groundbreaking, user-friendly urine test to detect early signs of kidney disease. This innovative biosensor measures SDMA, a more precise indicator of kidney health than traditional methods. The test's affordability, ease of use, and rapid results make it ideal for widespread use, potentially revolutionizing kidney disease diagnosis and treatment globally.
title: Now a non-invasive test to detect early signs of kidney problems

description: The Australian government is set to introduce legislation banning social media use for children under 16. The legislation aims to protect children from online harm, including cyberbullying, exposure to inappropriate content, and mental health issues. While the ban won't affect existing users, it has sparked debate about the potential impact on children's digital literacy and online safety education.
title: This country plans to ban social media for kids under 16

description: Freshworks, a US-based IT company, is laying off 13% of its workforce, or 660 employees, to streamline operations and prioritize its fastest-growing business areas. CEO Dennis Woodside announced the restructuring plan in a letter to staff, citing a need to focus on employee experience, AI, and customer experience.
title: Freshworks to layoff 660 employees: ‘There’s simply no ...,’ CEO in email

description: Shreyas Iyer smashed a double century (233 off 228) for Mumbai in the Ranji Trophy against Odisha on Thursday. This follows his previous century, signaling strong form ahead of the IPL auction.  His performance is a statement to both franchises and national selectors as he aims to regain his place in the Indian team.
title: Shreyas Iyer makes a big statement with 233 ahead of IPL auction

description: KL Rahul's hopes of securing a spot in the Indian Test team for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy suffered a setback as he was dismissed for just four runs in the India A warm-up match against Australia A at the Melbourne Cricket Ground. Rahul's inconsistent form continues to plague him, raising concerns about his readiness for the crucial Test series.
title: KL Rahul's inconsistent form continues

description: Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma is expected to miss the first Test against Australia in the Border Gavaskar Trophy due to personal reasons, widely believed to be the impending birth of his second child.
title: Aaron Finch disagrees with Sunil Gavaskar's comment on Rohit Sharma

description: The Supreme Court has scrapped the Jalan-Fritsch consortium's resolution plan for Jet Airways, leading to the airline's liquidation. The court overturned the NCLAT's decision, citing the consortium's failure to infuse funds as a key reason.  The court criticized the NCLAT's ruling and deemed liquidation as the best course of action for creditors and stakeholders.
title: SC orders liquidation of Jet Airways' assets, sets aside NCLAT decision

description: A Hindu priest in Brampton, Canada, was suspended after a clash erupted between pro-Khalistan protesters and temple attendees during an event with Indian consular officials. The incident involved physical altercations and prompted responses from Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and the Indian Ministry of External Affairs, both condemning the violence and calling for peace and accountability.
title: 'Can’t let agitators fuel flames of division': Hindu priest suspended in Canada

description: The Canadian government has ordered TikTok to cease operations in the country, citing national security risks posed by its Chinese owner, ByteDance.  This decision, based on intelligence assessments, follows a trend of countries restricting TikTok. While the app itself isn't banned for Canadian users, TikTok plans to challenge the order, warning of job losses.

description: Former Indian cricketer Aakash Chopra believes Rishabh Pant could become the IPL's most expensive player ever, potentially fetching over Rs 25 crore in the 2025 mega auction. Chopra cited Pant's stellar form and the substantial purses of teams like Punjab Kings and RCB as factors driving the potential bidding war.
title: 'Teams will go hammer & tongs': Chopra on Pant at IPL auction

description: India to play four T20 matches in South Africa. Suryakumar Yadav will captain the Indian team. The series starts on November 8. Matches will be played in Durban, Gqeberha, Centurion, and Johannesburg.  Suryakumar Yadav recently scored a century against South Africa. Kuldeep Yadav took five wickets in that match. The Indian squad has been announced.
title: What had happened when SKY last played a T20I in South Africa

description: The Australian government is set to introduce new laws banning children under 16 from using social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok. Citing concerns about harm to young users, Prime Minister Anthony Albanese emphasized the need to protect children from harmful content and unrealistic body image portrayals.
title: Australia to ban Facebook, Instagram and TikTok for these users

description: Music mogul Sean "Diddy" Combs faces serious legal challenges, including allegations of abuse, assault, and possession of explicit tapes involving celebrities, some potentially underage. description: Apple CEO Tim Cook extended his congratulations to Donald Trump on his victory in the US presidential election.  Cook expressed optimism about potential collaborations between the government and the tech industry, highlighting Apple's commitment to American progress.
title: Apple CEO congratulates Donald Trump; Elon Musk responds ...

description: Former New Zealand pacer Simon Doull believes Australia's strategic scheduling of the first three Tests, featuring fast and bouncy pitches in Perth, Adelaide (pink-ball Test), and Brisbane, is a deliberate ploy to "cook" Indian pace spearhead Jasprit Bumrah by forcing him to bear a heavy workload early in the series.
title: 'Australia trying to cook Bumrah with smart BGT scheduling'

description: The Jammu and Kashmir Assembly in Srinagar witnessed repeated disruptions as heated debates erupted over Article 370. MLA Khurshid Ahmad Sheikh's display of a banner supporting Article 370 drew objections, while Deputy Chief Minister Surinder Kumar Choudhary's resolution for its restoration sparked fierce opposition.
title: Watch: Massive ruckus in J&K assembly as MLAs clash over Article 370 banner

description: A Copa Airlines flight from Brazil to Panama experienced a harrowing near-disaster when a passenger, armed with a plastic knife, attempted to open the emergency door. Passengers bravely intervened, subduing the man until authorities apprehended him upon landing. The airline commended both the crew and passengers for their quick action in ensuring the safety of everyone on board.
title: Watch: Passenger attempts to open plane’s emergency door mid-air

description: Donald Trump, re-elected as the US President, received congratulatory messages from world leaders, including Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi, who expressed eagerness to strengthen bilateral ties. Trump's victory sparked optimism in US markets, with stocks and cryptocurrency surging. Meanwhile, Special Counsel Jack Smith is reportedly considering dropping federal cases against Trump, citing presidential immunity.

description: India and South Africa are gearing up for a thrilling four-match T20 series, starting Friday in Durban. The series is being seen as a rematch of the T20 World Cup final, where India emerged victorious. Team India boasts a strong winning streak in T20Is, while South Africa have struggled since their World Cup defeat.
title: T20 Form Guide: 'In-form' India hold a slight advantage vs South Africa

description: Following a violent disruption at a Hindu temple near Toronto, the Indian Consulate in Toronto has cancelled upcoming consular camps across Canada. The incident, condemned by both Indian and Canadian Prime Ministers, involved alleged attacks on women and children by pro-Khalistani groups, sparking protests and calls for increased security for the Indian diaspora.
title: 'Inability to provide security': Indian consulate in Canada cancels consular camps

description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz dismissed Finance Minister Christian Lindner, leading to the collapse of the ruling coalition. Scholz cited policy clashes and plans to seek a vote of confidence in January, potentially triggering early elections amid economic concerns and global uncertainty.
title: German govt in crisis as Scholz’s ruling coalition collapses: Key details

description: West Indies pacer Alzarri Joseph briefly left the field during the third ODI against England after a disagreement with captain Shai Hope over field placement. Despite taking a wicket in the same over, Joseph appeared frustrated and exited the field. He later returned and completed his 10-over spell, contributing to West Indies' comfortable eight-wicket victory and series win.

description: Former Australian cricketer, Greg Chappell, has extended his support to struggling Indian batsman Prithvi Shaw through a heartfelt letter. Chappell encourages Shaw to view his recent exclusion from the Mumbai Ranji Trophy team as a turning point, drawing parallels to the setbacks faced by cricketing legends like Don Bradman.
title: Chappell to Shaw: Pain of discipline better than pain of regret

description: Anees Bazmee's 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' emerged as the highest-grossing film on Wednesday, narrowly surpassing Rohit Shetty's 'Singham Again.' Despite experiencing a decline in earnings after a strong opening weekend, 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' earned an estimated Rs 10.50 crore on its sixth day, bringing its total collection to around Rs 148.50 crore.
title: 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' Day 6 collection: Kartik Aaryan starrer beats 'Singham Again'

description: Several prominent Indian-Americans congratulated Donald Trump on his re-election as US President. They expressed their eagerness to collaborate with his administration in strengthening US-India relations and advancing shared global interests. Figures like Vivek Ramaswamy, Sunder Pichai, and Satya Nadella were among those who publicly conveyed their well-wishes and support.

description: Melania Trump, in her first public statement since her husband's re-election, expressed optimism for the future and called for national unity. She emphasized the importance of individual liberty, economic prosperity, and security, urging Americans to rise above ideology.  Trump's victory speech echoed these sentiments, promising a new era focused on national healing and renewal.
title: Melania's first message after Trump gets re-elected as president

description: Election officials have confiscated over Rs 588 crore worth of illicit goods intended to sway voters in upcoming elections in Maharashtra and Jharkhand, as well as bypolls in 14 other states.  Seizures, including cash, alcohol, drugs, and freebies, have significantly increased compared to the previous elections in 2019, indicating a heightened effort to curb the influence of money in politics.

description: Vivek Ramaswamy, a rising Republican star, attributes Donald Trump's recent political victory to his resilience and embodiment of the "American badass" spirit.  Ramaswamy believes Trump's appeal lies in his defiance of expectations and his connection with the strength and exceptionalism of the American people.  Meanwhile, Vice President Kamala Harris conceded defeat while promising to continue advocating for progressive values.

description: Former Australian cricketer Michael Clarke believes fatigue played a role in India's recent loss to New Zealand, but expects a strong comeback in the Border-Gavaskar series. Meanwhile, Aaron Finch disagrees with Sunil Gavaskar's suggestion that Jasprit Bumrah should captain India for the entire series if Rohit Sharma misses games due to personal reasons.

description: Former President Barack Obama congratulated Trump and Vance on their victory while acknowledging the disappointment of those hoping for a different outcome. He emphasized the importance of a peaceful transfer of power and urged Americans to address challenges with unity and grace. Vice president Harris also conceded, promising to continue fighting for the causes her campaign championed.

description: Jeff Bezos, founder of Amazon, congratulated Donald Trump on his victory in the US presidential election, praising his "extraordinary political comeback." Bezos, despite a history of disagreements with Trump, expressed hope for collaboration with the new administration on key issues. Notably, Bezos' Washington Post refrained from endorsing any presidential candidate, emphasizing its commitment to impartiality.

description: The Madras High Court has ordered Telegram to block and remove channels impersonating PhonePe to defraud users. PhonePe, a digital payments platform, filed a lawsuit alleging financial losses due to these scam channels.

description: The Supreme Court has allowed the Ajit Pawar-led NCP faction to use the 'clock' symbol for the Maharashtra assembly elections. This decision comes after the faction assured the court that it would publish a disclaimer in leading newspapers, clarifying that the legal battle with Sharad Pawar over the party's control and symbol is still ongoing.

description: India engaged in its first meeting with Taliban's acting defense minister, Mohammad Yaqub Mujahid, in Kabul on Wednesday.  The meeting aimed to strengthen bilateral relations, focusing on humanitarian cooperation and other key areas.  India is considering increasing its role in Afghanistan's reconstruction, encouraged by the Taliban's assurances of preventing anti-India activities on Afghan soil.

description: Indian National Congress leaders, including party chief Mallikarjun Kharge and Rahul Gandhi, extended their congratulations to Donald Trump on his election victory. They expressed optimism for continued collaboration between India and the US, emphasizing the strong bilateral ties and shared values between the two nations.

description: Maharashtra Chief Minister Eknath Shinde dismissed rumors of infighting within the Mahayuti alliance, stating their sole focus is regaining power in the upcoming assembly elections.  Confident in his government's performance and welfare schemes, Shinde believes the Mahayuti will secure a comfortable majority. He refuted claims of industry exodus under his leadership, highlighting Maharashtra's significant investment influx and economic dominance.
title: No clamour for CM post, win for Mahayuti is top priority: Shinde

description: India A's batting lineup crumbled against Australia A's pace attack on the first day of the second unofficial Test in Melbourne. Michael Neser and Scott Boland ripped through India's top order, leaving them reeling at 11/4 inside three overs. KL Rahul, being tested as a potential opener for the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy, managed just 4 runs before edging Boland behind.

description: A woman named Swati Mukund has accused BharatMatrimony of using her photo without consent on a fake profile for their premium service.
title: Married woman slams Bharatmatrimony: This is post on India’s...

description: Elon Musk enthusiastically supported Donald Trump's presidential campaign, anticipating a role in his administration that would grant him influence over policies impacting his businesses. Trump, in return, pledged to appoint Musk to a cost-cutting position and praised his SpaceX ventures.
title: Three things that Donald Trump and Elon Musk may not agree on

description: Donald Trump's potential second term as US president could see stricter immigration policies, impacting Indian IT firms reliant on H-1B visas. Despite these firms reducing visa dependency, experts predict tighter regulations and potential hurdles for international workers under a new Trump administration.
title: Indian IT companies brace for tighter visa guidelines

description: Bitcoin soared to an all-time high, driven by Trump's projected victory and the anticipation of favorable cryptocurrency regulations during his potential second term. The cryptocurrency market responded positively to Trump's pro-crypto stance, contrasting with the stricter approach adopted by the Biden administration.
title: Bitcoin scales $75k peak as 'crypto prez' romps home

description: The Indian rupee experienced its most significant drop in over four months, closing at 84.28 against the US dollar due to Trump's victory. Despite this decline, the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) intervened to curb further depreciation.  Global currencies also faced significant losses against a strengthening dollar, fueled by anxieties surrounding potential trade barriers. The Mexican peso, euro, Chinese yuan, and South African rand were among the most affected.

description: Economists and market analysts believe that a return of Donald Trump to the White House could bring both opportunities and challenges for the Indian market. While some sectors like software and pharmaceuticals might benefit, others could face tariff barriers. Despite potential volatility, India is expected to attract foreign investment due to its favorable policies and the 'China +1' strategy.

description: The article narrates the unconventional love story of JD Vance, the US Vice President-elect, and his wife, Usha Chilukuri, an Indian-American attorney. Hailing from contrasting backgrounds, their paths crossed at Yale Law School. Despite their differences, they formed a deep bond, leading to marriage in 2014. Usha played a pivotal role in JD's life, guiding him through social situations and providing unwavering support.

description: India welcomes Donald Trump's return to the White House, viewing it as a positive development due to his previous alignment with India's strategic interests and strong rapport with Prime Minister Narendra Modi.  Former officials believe Trump will resume strengthening ties with India, particularly in counterterrorism and addressing Chinese influence in the Indo-Pacific region.

description: RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das warns of escalating inflation, projecting October figures to surpass September's 5.49%.  Despite mixed economic data, Das maintains a cautious stance on rate cuts, emphasizing a need for sustained observation amidst global uncertainties and commodity price fluctuations.
title: Inflation to be higher in Oct, eco giving mixed signals: Shaktikanta Das

description: Rajesaheb Deshmukh, an NCP(SCP) candidate in Parli, made an unusual campaign promise. He pledged to help bachelors find spouses and livelihoods. Deshmukh is challenging the incumbent MLA, Dhananjay Munde. Munde highlighted his achievements in office, including establishing industries and educational institutions. Parli is experiencing a caste-based political divide.
